{"parse":{"title":"Standpipe (street)","pageid":11524334,"revid":860065907,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:152px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Bad_Duerrenberg_Wasserhahn.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7a/Bad_Duerrenberg_Wasserhahn.jpg/150px-Bad_Duerrenberg_Wasserhahn.jpg\" width=\"150\" height=\"214\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7a/Bad_Duerrenberg_Wasserhahn.jpg/225px-Bad_Duerrenberg_Wasserhahn.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7a/Bad_Duerrenberg_Wasserhahn.jpg/300px-Bad_Duerrenberg_Wasserhahn.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"1890\" data-file-height=\"2700\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Bad_Duerrenberg_Wasserhahn.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Standpipe in <a href=\"/wiki/Bad_D%C3%BCrrenberg\" title=\"Bad D\u00fcrrenberg\">Bad D\u00fcrrenberg</a></div></div></div>\n<p>A <b>standpipe</b> is a freestanding pipe fitted with a <a href=\"/wiki/Tap_(valve)\" title=\"Tap (valve)\">tap</a> which is installed outdoors to dispense <a href=\"/wiki/Water\" title=\"Water\">water</a> in areas which do not have a running water supply to the buildings.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Use\">Use</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Standpipe_(street)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Use\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>In the <a href=\"/wiki/United_Kingdom\" title=\"United Kingdom\">United Kingdom</a>, an \"Emergency Drought Order\" permits a water company to shut off the primary water supply to homes, and to supply water instead from tanks or standpipes in the streets. This was done in some areas during the <a href=\"/wiki/1976_United_Kingdom_heat_wave\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"1976 United Kingdom heat wave\">1976 heat wave</a>, for example.\n</p><p>In some <a href=\"/wiki/Middle_East\" title=\"Middle East\">Middle Eastern</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Caribbean\" title=\"Caribbean\">Caribbean</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/North_Africa\" title=\"North Africa\">North African</a> countries a standpipe is used as a communal <a href=\"/wiki/Water_supply\" title=\"Water supply\">water supply</a> for neighbourhoods which lack individual housing <a href=\"/wiki/Water_service\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Water service\">water service</a>. In areas such as Morocco, standpipes often yield unreliable service and lead to <a href=\"/wiki/Water_scarcity\" title=\"Water scarcity\">water scarcity</a> for large numbers of people.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Benoit_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Benoit-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> This outcome is not based upon the unreliability of the hardware, but on the underlying condition of the <a href=\"/wiki/Human_overpopulation\" title=\"Human overpopulation\">population exceeding</a> the <a href=\"/wiki/Carrying_capacity\" title=\"Carrying capacity\">carrying capacity</a> of the region with respect to <a href=\"/wiki/Water_resources\" title=\"Water resources\">water resources</a>.\n</p>\n<ul class=\"gallery mw-gallery-packed\">\n\t\t<li class=\"gallerybox\" style=\"width: 162px\"><div style=\"width: 162px\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"thumb\" style=\"width: 160px;\"><div style=\"margin:0px auto;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Standpipe_in_winter_wonderland_Helsinki.JPG\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/01/Standpipe_in_winter_wonderland_Helsinki.JPG/240px-Standpipe_in_winter_wonderland_Helsinki.JPG\" width=\"160\" height=\"120\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/01/Standpipe_in_winter_wonderland_Helsinki.JPG/360px-Standpipe_in_winter_wonderland_Helsinki.JPG 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/01/Standpipe_in_winter_wonderland_Helsinki.JPG/480px-Standpipe_in_winter_wonderland_Helsinki.JPG 2x\" data-file-width=\"3648\" data-file-height=\"2736\" /></a></div></div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"gallerytext\">\n<p>Standpipe in <a href=\"/wiki/Helsinki\" title=\"Helsinki\">Helsinki</a>\n</p>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div></li>\n\t\t<li class=\"gallerybox\" style=\"width: 162px\"><div style=\"width: 162px\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"thumb\" style=\"width: 160px;\"><div style=\"margin:0px auto;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Standpipe_1.JPG\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2b/Standpipe_1.JPG/240px-Standpipe_1.JPG\" width=\"160\" height=\"120\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2b/Standpipe_1.JPG/360px-Standpipe_1.JPG 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2b/Standpipe_1.JPG/480px-Standpipe_1.JPG 2x\" data-file-width=\"2816\" data-file-height=\"2112\" /></a></div></div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"gallerytext\">\n<p>A standpipe in Russia\n</p>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div></li>\n\t\t<li class=\"gallerybox\" style=\"width: 69.333333333333px\"><div style=\"width: 69.333333333333px\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"thumb\" style=\"width: 67.333333333333px;\"><div style=\"margin:0px auto;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Borne_de_puisage_BAYARD.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b9/Borne_de_puisage_BAYARD.jpg/101px-Borne_de_puisage_BAYARD.jpg\" width=\"68\" height=\"120\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b9/Borne_de_puisage_BAYARD.jpg/152px-Borne_de_puisage_BAYARD.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b9/Borne_de_puisage_BAYARD.jpg/202px-Borne_de_puisage_BAYARD.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"1746\" data-file-height=\"3104\" /></a></div></div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"gallerytext\">\n<p>Standpipe to draw water on public urban street in France\n</p>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div></li>\n\t\t<li class=\"gallerybox\" style=\"width: 92px\"><div style=\"width: 92px\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"thumb\" style=\"width: 90px;\"><div style=\"margin:0px auto;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Standpipe.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/ba/Standpipe.jpg/135px-Standpipe.jpg\" width=\"90\" height=\"120\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/ba/Standpipe.jpg/202px-Standpipe.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/ba/Standpipe.jpg/270px-Standpipe.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"1920\" data-file-height=\"2560\" /></a></div></div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"gallerytext\">\n<p>Standpipe at a backyard in Argentina\n</p>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div></li>\n</ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Standpipe_(street)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Benoit-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-Benoit_1-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Guillaume Benoit and Aline Comeau, <i>A Sustainable Future for the Mediterranean</i> (2005) 640 pages</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<table role=\"presentation\" class=\"mbox-small plainlinks sistersitebox\" style=\"background-color:#f9f9f9;border:1px solid #aaa;color:#000\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<td class=\"mbox-image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/4a/Commons-logo.svg/30px-Commons-logo.svg.png\" width=\"30\" height=\"40\" class=\"noviewer\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/4a/Commons-logo.svg/45px-Commons-logo.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/4a/Commons-logo.svg/59px-Commons-logo.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"1024\" data-file-height=\"1376\" /></td>\n<td class=\"mbox-text plai